The paper deals with combinatorial structures related to parent-identifying schemes, which are used in information systems such as digital fingerprinting and group testing. This suggests that the paper may belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), Multimedia (cs.MM), or Computational Complexity (cs.CC) sub-categories. The paper specifically mentions broadcast encryption and multimedia fingerprinting, which are topics related to multimedia and information theory. Therefore, cs.IT and cs.MM are the most likely sub-categories. However, the paper also discusses forbidden configurations, which are related to computational complexity and data structures. Therefore, cs.CR, cs.DS, and cs.CC are also likely sub-categories.
